<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-07-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-07-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="407" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d407">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.001 BG4/1.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 147.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-07-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 8, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I enclose, with office copy, a
                                letter<note n="1" xml:id="d407fn1">Not printed.</note> addressed by
                            the President to His Excellency General José Bordas Valdes,
                            acknowledging His Excellency’s letter of April 14, last in which he
                            announced his assumption of the Presidency of the Dominican Republic,
                            and his entrance upon the duties of that office.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>(For the Secretary of State:) <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Moore</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>